.TH UDR 1 "July 2026" "udr v1.4.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
udr \- Universal Dependency Resolver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B udr
[\fI\-\-version\fR] [\fI\-\-help\fR] [\fI\-\-offline\fR]
\fI<command>\fR [\fI<args>\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBUniversal Dependency Resolver (UDR)\fR is a cross-ecosystem dependency
resolution tool that resolves, locks, and manages dependencies across 27
package ecosystems. It uses an AutoSolver (profiles workload, delegates to
PubGrub/Z3/Hybrid) with SCC batch partitioning, CUDA-aware conflict
resolution, and DFS backtracking to produce consistent, reproducible lock
files.

UDR supports in-place manifest updates, CVE scanning, license compliance
checking, SBOM generation (SPDX/CycloneDX), supply chain attestation with
Ed25519 signing, policy enforcement, cross-compilation targeting, offline-
first indexed caches, and per-ecosystem solver isolation.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lock
Resolve dependencies and write a lock file
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-manifest\fR, \fB\-\-export\fR, \fB\-\-cuda\fR,
\fB\-\-device\fR, \fB\-\-target\fR, \fB\-\-platform\fR,
\fB\-\-sign\fR, \fB\-\-provenance\fR, \fB\-\-check\fR,
\fB\-\-workspace\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR, \fB\-\-dry-run\fR,
\fB\-\-timeout\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR, \fB\-\-auto-sync\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B install
Install dependencies from a lock file
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-ecosystem\fR, \fB\-\-dry-run\fR, \fB\-\-production\fR,
\fB\-\-cuda\fR, \fB\-\-target\fR, \fB\-\-platform\fR,
\fB\-\-workspace\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B resolve
Resolve dependencies without writing a lock file
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-ecosystem\fR, \fB\-\-format\fR, \fB\-\-cuda\fR,
\fB\-\-device\fR, \fB\-\-target\fR, \fB\-\-platform\fR,
\fB\-\-timeout\fR, \fB\-\-interactive\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B scan
Scan a project directory for manifests and detect ecosystems
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-ecosystem\fR, \fB\-\-format\fR, \fB\-\-cuda\fR,
\fB\-\-device\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B update
Update manifest files from a lock file
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-interactive\fR, \fB\-\-dry-run\fR, \fB\-\-cuda\fR,
\fB\-\-device\fR, \fB\-\-target\fR, \fB\-\-platform\fR,
\fB\-\-fix-cve\fR, \fB\-\-workspace\fR, \fB\-\-lock-file\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B graph
Print a dependency tree / graph
.RS
Outputs ASCII or DOT-format dependency graph.
.RE
.TP
.B serve
Start the UDR API server
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-host\fR, \fB\-\-port\fR, \fB\-\-reload\fR,
\fB\-\-mode\fR (local|saas), \fB\-\-workers\fR,
\fB\-\-ssl-keyfile\fR, \fB\-\-ssl-certfile\fR,
\fB\-\-log-level\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B why
Show why a package is required (dependency chain + constraint trace)
.RS
Takes a package name; \fB\-\-all\fR shows all chains.
.RE
.TP
.B details
Display detailed package information
.RE
.TP
.B diff
Compare two lock files or workspace lock files
.RS
\fBudr diff [old] [new]\fR or \fB\-\-workspace\fR convenience mode.
.RE
.TP
.B outdated
List outdated packages from a lock file
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-json\fR for machine-readable output.
.RE
.TP
.B search
Search for packages across registries
.RE
.TP
.B check
Check system compatibility, CVEs, licenses, deprecated packages, or policy
.RS
Flags: \fB\-\-cve\fR, \fB\-\-license\fR, \fB\-\-deprecated\fR,
\fB\-\-policy\fR, \fB\-\-deps\fR, \fB\-\-cuda\fR,
\fB\-\-device\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR,
\fB\-\-workspace\fR, \fB\-\-lock-file\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B verify
Verify lock file integrity and (optionally) Ed25519 signatures
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-json\fR, \fB\-\-signature\fR, \fB\-\-workspace\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B list-ecosystems
List all supported ecosystems with their registries
.RE
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, or fish
.RS
Usage: \fBudr completion bash\fR | \fBzsh\fR | \fBfish\fR
.RE
.TP
.B auth
Manage API keys and signing keys (gen-key, show-key)
.RE
.TP
.B index
Manage offline package indexes (build, sync, info)
.RE
.TP
.B sbom
Generate an SBOM in SPDX 2.3 or CycloneDX 1.5 format
.RS
Supports \fB\-\-format\fR (spdx|cyclonedx), \fB\-\-output\fR,
\fB\-\-workspace\fR, \fB\-\-lock-file\fR.
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-offline
Use cached data only; no network requests.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I udr.lock
Universal lock file (JSON) containing resolved dependency graph, integrity
hashes, and provenance metadata.
.TP
.I udr\-policy.yaml
YAML policy file for \fBudr check \-\-policy\fR with rules for allowed
licenses, blocked packages, vulnerability thresholds, etc.
.TP
.I ~/.config/udr/
User configuration directory containing:
.RS
.TP
.I keys/
Ed25519 signing keypair for lock file attestation.
.TP
.I config.toml
Optional user preferences (defaults to env vars).
.RE
.TP
.I ~/.cache/udr/
Cache directory for API responses and offline indexes.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B USE_Z3_SOLVER
Set to "true" to force Z3 solver instead of default PubGrub.
.TP
.B USE_PUBGRUB_SOLVER
Set to "true" (default false) to enable PubGrub solver.
.TP
.B SOLVER_TIMEOUT
Overall resolution timeout in seconds (default 60).
.TP
.B SOLVER_MAX_VARIABLES
Maximum SAT variables before solver gives up (default 50000).
.TP
.B SOLVER_REJECT_DEPRECATED
Reject deprecated/yanked packages during resolution (default false,
warn only).
.TP
.B SOLVER_OPTIMIZATION_THRESHOLD
Version count above which Z3 optimization is disabled (default 100).
.TP
.B BFS_BATCH_SIZE
Parallel batch size for BFS dependency fetching (default 20).
.TP
.B PIN_INTEGRITY
Set to "true" to verify package integrity hashes (default false).
.TP
.B NPM_CONCURRENCY
Max concurrent npm API requests (default 10).
.TP
.B TARGET_OS
Override target OS for cross-compilation (linux|windows|darwin).
.TP
.B TARGET_ARCH
Override target architecture (x86_64|aarch64|arm64|i386|amd64).
.TP
.B TARGET_CUDA
Override target CUDA version for cross-compilation.
.TP
.B DETECT_ECOSYSTEMS_TIMEOUT
Timeout in seconds for ecosystem detection probes (default 15).
.TP
.B RETRY_MAX_DELAY
Maximum retry backoff delay in seconds (default 10).
.TP
.B INDEX_AUTO_SYNC
Set to "true" to auto-sync stale indexes before resolution (default false).
.TP
.BI {ECOSYSTEM}_AUTH_TOKEN
Authentication token for a specific ecosystem registry.
.BI {ECOSYSTEM}_AUTH_TYPE
Auth type: bearer (default), basic, or header.
.BI {ECOSYSTEM}_AUTH_USERNAME
Username for basic auth.
.BI {ECOSYSTEM}_AUTH_PASSWORD
Password for basic auth.
.PD
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Resolve and lock dependencies
.B udr lock
.TP
Resolve with CUDA 12.1 and JSON output
.B udr lock --cuda 12.1 --json
.TP
Cross-compile for ARM Linux
.B udr lock --target linux --platform aarch64
.TP
Check for CVEs
.B udr check --cve
.TP
Check license compliance
.B udr check --license
.TP
Check policy
.B udr check --policy udr-policy.yaml
.TP
Generate SBOM
.B udr sbom --format spdx --output bom.json
.TP
Update manifests from lock file
.B udr update
.TP
Fix vulnerable packages automatically
.B udr update --fix-cve
.TP
Sign lock file
.B udr lock --sign
.TP
Verify signed lock file
.B udr verify --signature
.TP
CI drift check (exit 1 if lock file is stale)
.B udr lock --check
.TP
Show why flask is required
.B udr why flask
.TP
Compare workspace lock files
.B udr diff --workspace backend
.TP
Generate bash completions
.B udr completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/udr
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR udr.lock (5),
.BR udr-policy.yaml (5),
.BR https://opencode.ai
